parameters: \p3Here's the peak of the pyramid. And... it
looks like there's a reward for our efforts.
\-I do not have a traditional name. At
least, I can no longer recall it.
as "The Warden". I am the guardian
for that! Can you give it to us?
pretty important though. We'd like it.
\wardIf you die with the hourglass in your
possession, no one will ever find it
again, damning those poor souls to an
eternity of wandering the fort's halls.
\wardThe hourglass was forged with the glistening
sands by the same mages who created them.
\wardThe mages enchanted and attuned it to their
place in the timeline as a last resort. They
wanted to ensure they wouldn't be cursed with
the fate of never dying all the way.
\wardI was one of the mages. On that blessed
night, I made the hike to this pyramid.
I have awaited a worthy challenger to
take it from me for a millenium.
\wardThe gauntlet within this pyramid is a
test of an adventurer's strength and mind.
However, your final trial still awaits.
\wardIn the centuries I have spent waiting
for someone worthy to arrive, I have
grown my strength to its absolute peak.
\wardIn my fall to the dark arts, I've
found more power than I ever thought
\wardI've amassed an army of supernatural beings,
mere shells of the souls belonging to those
that have been buried in the pyramid.
\wardAll of this preparation and power only
exists for one reason: to test you.
\wardI have great respect for your strength,
travelers. I sincerely hope you are able
to strike me down and take this hourglass.
\wardBut if you are not truly worthy...
then I will kill you quickly to spare
you from the pain of death.
